<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1401">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 381.81F47/1.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 20, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Regarding the American protégé, Mohammed ben Lehsen el Filaly, the French
                            officers concerned have apologized and report that the Court Martial
                            have decided not to prosecute him. My British colleague has asked for
                            instructions as to his nationals in any smilar situation, and although
                            the present case is apparently closed I also should appreciate
                            instructions as to future questions of a like nature.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Carpenter.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>